"title": "5959: submission",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5959",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A humble attitude where obedience is rendered within a relationship; whether it be to God, authorities or other people at work, in the church, in marriage or in the family.</p>\n<h2>God requires submission</h2>\n<h3>From all people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps2:9-Ps2:11\">PSA 2:9–2:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job22:21\">JOB 22:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:6\">1PE 5:6</a></p>\n<h3>From Christians especially</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:9-Matt6:10\">MAT 6:9–6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:9\">HEB 12:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:7\">JAS 4:7</a></p>\n<h2>The submission of Jesus Christ to his Father</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:42\">LUK 22:42</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:39\">MAT 26:39</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:36\">MRK 14:36</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John5:19\">JHN 5:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:49-John12:50\">JHN 12:49–12:50</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:27-1Cor15:28\">1CO 15:27–15:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:7-Heb5:8\">HEB 5:7–5:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:5-Heb10:7\">HEB 10:5–10:7</a></p>\n<h2>The submissive spirit required in the church</h2>\n<h3>In believers' relationships with one another</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:21\">EPH 5:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:5-Phil2:7\">PHP 2:5–2:7</a></p>\n<h3>To Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:24\">EPH 5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:22-Eph1:23\">EPH 1:22–1:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:18\">COL 1:18</a> <em>As the body is subject to the head, so the church is subject to Christ.</em></p>\n<h3>To the Scriptures</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:7-Josh1:8\">JOS 1:7–1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:133\">PSA 119:133</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:15\">COL 3:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:22-Jas1:25\">JAS 1:22–1:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev22:18-Rev22:19\">REV 22:18–22:19</a></p>\n<h3>To church leaders</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:17\">HEB 13:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor16:15-1Cor16:16\">1CO 16:15–16:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:12-1Thess5:13\">1TH 5:12–5:13</a></p>\n<h3>In prophecy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:32\">1CO 14:32</a></strong> <em>The implication is that individual prophecies must be submitted to the overall judgment of the church.</em></p>\n<h2>The submission of all to civil government</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:21\">MAT 22:21</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:17\">MRK 12:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:25\">LUK 20:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:2-Rom13:7\">ROM 13:2–13:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:1\">TIT 3:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:14\">1PE 2:13–2:14</a></p>\n<h2>Submission within other relationships</h2>\n<h3>Of wives to husbands</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:22-Eph5:24\">EPH 5:22–5:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:18\">COL 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:4-Titus2:5\">TIT 2:4–2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:1\">1PE 3:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:5-1Pet3:6\">1PE 3:5–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>Of children to parents</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:1-Eph6:3\">EPH 6:1–6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:2\">GAL 4:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:20\">COL 3:20</a></p>\n<h3>Of slaves to masters</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:5-Eph6:8\">EPH 6:5–6:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:22-Col3:24\">COL 3:22–3:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:9-Titus2:10\">TIT 2:9–2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:18\">1PE 2:18</a></p>\n<h3>Of young to old</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:5\">1PE 5:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:32\">LEV 19:32</a></p>\n<h3>Reciprocal attitudes are commended to safeguard against abuse</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:25-Eph5:33\">EPH 5:25–5:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:4\">EPH 6:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph6:9\">EPH 6:9</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:1–2:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet5:1-1Pet5:4\">1PE 5:1–5:4</a> <em>Those in authority have a responsibility to set an example.</em></p>",
